13/01/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Israel and Greece agreed on Wednesday (January 12th) to set up a joint ministerial commission in a bid to strengthen bilateral ties.
The announcement came as Israeli Foreign Minister Avigdor Lieberman kicked off a two-day visit to Athens, the first by an Israeli foreign minister in over 15 years.
Greek counterpart Dimitris Droutsas said the first meeting of the new commission will be held in Israel in the next few months.
He and Lieberman also vowed to boost economic co-operation.
(VoA, AP, AFP - 12/01/11)
